==English==
===Etymology===
Latin [[aleatorius]], from [[aleator]] ‘dice-player’, from [[alea]] ‘a die’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'eɪlɪətəri/

===Adjective===
'''aleatory'''
# depending on the throw of a [[die]]; [[random]], arising by [[chance]]
===Noun===
# {{music}} aleatory or [[aleatoric music]], meaning [[chance music]] in which the [[performer]]s are free to perform their own [[material]] and/or their own [[manner]] of [[presentation]].

